# AI Agent Guidelines (.clinerules)

This file applies to all autonomous or agentic coding assistants (using Claude, GPT, or Gemini) working in this repository.

## 1. CRITICAL CONSTRAINTS (NO EXCEPTIONS)
* **DO NOT BUILD**: AI must **NEVER** run any build, compile, or configuration commands (e.g., `cmake`, `msbuild`, `dotnet`, `make`). The user handles all compilation manually.
* **DO NOT TEST**: AI must **NEVER** run any automated testing suites (e.g., `ctest`, `dotnet test`).
* **DO NOT PUSH**: AI must **NEVER** run `git push`. All remote operations are handled by the user.
* **ASK IF UNSURE**: If there is any ambiguity, doubt, or missing requirements, the AI must stop and ask clarifying questions instead of guessing.

## 2. CODE STYLE & ARCHITECTURE RULES
- **Exit Early**: Place guard conditions at the top of C++ and C# functions (`if (bad) return;`). Avoid deep nesting.
- **Short Functions**: Keep functions short (max 40 lines). Extract logical blocks on touch.
- **No Magic Numbers**: Give numbers, colors, times, and array offsets descriptive named constants (`constexpr` / `const` / `enum`).
- **No Heap Allocations in Hot Paths**: Inside rendering loops or per-frame character updates, do NOT allocate memory on the heap (avoid constructing `std::vector`, `std::string`, or using `new`).
- **One Class per File**: Separate C++ classes into matching `.h`/`.cpp` files. Keep one public type per C# file.

